    "details": {
      "en": {
        "id": "en",
        "purpose": "The STOP-Bang questionnaire is a scoring model consisting of eight easily administered questions starting with the acronym STOP-Bang and is scored based on Yes/No answers each yes sums up 1 point. A score of ≥3 has shown a high sensitivity for detecting OSA: 93% and 100% for moderate and severe OSA, respectively. (1)",
        "keywords": [
          "Polysomnography ",
          "Sleep Apnea, Obstructive / epidemiology",
          "Sleep Apnea, Obstructive / physiopathology",
          "mass screening",
          "questionnaires",
          "sleep apnea",
          "snoring/di (diagnosis)",
          "snoring/ep (epidemiology)"
        ],
        "use": "-Patients undergoing preoperative evaluation.\n-Patients presenting to a clinic setting with symptoms associated with OSA like: daytime drowsiness, snoring, observed periods of nighttime apnea, noisy breathing, etc.",
        "misuse": "- Not well validated in the obstetrical population, a subgroup with increased risk of OSA.\n- If a patient has already been diagnosed with OSA or uses CPAP at night.\n- Not for central sleep apnea."
      },
      "es": {
        "id": "es",
        "purpose": "El cuestionario STOP-Bang es un modelo de calificación que consta de ocho preguntas fáciles de administrar que comienzan con el acrónimo STOP-Bang y se puntúa en base a respuestas Sí/No, cada sí suma 1 punto. Una puntuación de ≥3 ha mostrado una alta sensibilidad para detectar AOS: 93 % y 100 % para AOS moderado y grave, respectivamente. (1)",
        "keywords": [
          "Apnea del Sueño Obstructiva / fisiopatología",
          " Apnea del Sueño Obstructiva / epidemiología",
          " Polisomnografía",
          " tamizaje masivo",
          " cuestionarios",
          "Apnea del sueño",
          " ronquido/di (diagnóstico)",
          " ronquido/ep (epidemiología)"
        ],
        "use": "-Pacientes sometidos a evaluación preoperatoria\n-Pacientes que acuden a un entorno clínico con síntomas asociados con AOS como: somnolencia diurna, ronquidos, periodos observados de apnea nocturna, respiración ruidosa, etc.",
        "misuse": "- Uso no validado en población obstétrica, un subgrupo con alto riesgo de AOS.\n- Si el paciente ya fue diagnosticado con AOS o usa un CPAP por las noches.\n- No apto para apnea central del sueño"
      }
    },
    "other_details": {
      "references": "1. Chung, F., Subramanyam, R., Liao, P., Sasaki, E., Shapiro, C., & Sun, Y. (2012). High STOP-Bang score indicates a high probability of obstructive sleep apnoea. British journal of anaesthesia, 108(5), 768–775. https://doi.org/10.1093/bja/aes022\n2.Nagappa, M., Liao, P., Wong, J., Auckley, D., Ramachandran, S. K., Memtsoudis, S., Mokhlesi, B., & Chung, F. (2015). Validation of the STOP-Bang Questionnaire as a Screening Tool for Obstructive Sleep Apnea among Different Populations: A Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis. PloS one, 10(12), e0143697. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0143697\n3.Doshi, V., Walia, R., Jones, K., Aston, C. E., & Awab, A. (2015). STOP-BANG questionnaire as a screening tool for diagnosis of obstructive sleep apnea by unattended portable monitoring sleep study. SpringerPlus, 4, 795. https://doi.org/10.1186/s40064-015-1588-0"
    }
  },
